🧱 Example: The Iliad

You don’t just “make a movie.”

You build layers:

⸻

1. Invariant Extraction (Anchor layer)

From text:
	•	characters (Achilles, Hector, etc.)
	•	relationships
	•	key events
	•	sequence/timing

From history:
	•	armor types
	•	geography (Troy region)
	•	combat style
	•	cultural norms

👉 This is your Certainty Wraith (Anchor)

⸻

2. Possibility Expansion (Wraith layer)

Where text is vague:
	•	exact facial features
	•	lighting conditions
	•	minor blocking
	•	environmental detail

You generate:
	•	multiple plausible interpretations

👉 This is your Probability Wraith

⸻

3. Convergence

Probability proposes → Certainty constrains → output scene


